result.execSummary:
The defendant Tamera Denise Dickey was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Criminal Damage to Property [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).
  • Knowingly Violate a Domestic Abuse Order - Injunction [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 813.12(8)(a).
  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

  DOC agent also in court.
Based upon the defendant's compliance with the conditions of probation, the Court ordered that time in the House of Correction, which was ordered as a condition of probation but stayed to today's date, be stayed for use at the agent's discretion in the future.

Sentencing Proceeded. Statements by parties and defendant. Defendant's grandmother addressed the court.
AS TO COUNT 1
The court sentenced the defendant to 5 MONTHS in the House of Correction, concurrent, credit for 1 Day time served, with Huber privileges for work.  Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 12 MONTHS.
AS TO COUNT 2
The court sentenced the defendant to 2 MONTHS in the House of Correction, concurrent, credit for 1 Day time served, with Huber privileges for work.  Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 12 MONTHS.
AS TO COUNT 3
The court sentenced the defendant to 3 MONTHS in the House of Correction, concurrent, credit for 1 Day time served, with Huber privileges for work.  Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 12 MONTHS.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION
-Serve 40 DAYS as Condition Time, STAYED pending review.
-A course in anger management.
-Parenting classes.
-Mental health evaluation, take all prescribed medications.
-AODA assessment, comply with recommended treatment.
-Absolute sobriety, random urine screens.
-Treatment and/or counseling as determined by agent.
-No contact with R.R.A., or M.W., unless approved by court or agent. 
-Court grants third party contact for time with the children, if allowed by Family Court.
-Obtain/maintain employment.
-No contact with firearms.
-Pay all MANDATORY court costs, fees, and surcharges including: DNA & DV (where applicable) surcharges during period of probation, failure to pay will result in a civil judgment. 
-Court WAIVED all NON-Mandatory court costs, fees, and surcharges due to inability to pay.

*Court allows transfer of probation to Dane County, if accepted.
*Court advised defendant of right to seek post conviction relief.

Filed: 
-Pretrial Sentence Credit
-Notice of Right to Seek Post-Conviction Relief

AS TO COUNTS 1, 2 & 3
Defendant changes plea(s) to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to plea, advised of Constitutional Rights and the maximum penalties. Court found that the defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived rights.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights form, received and filed. Parties stipulate to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea(s).  Court found defendant GUILTY and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.

Defendant Tamera Denise Dickey in court with attorney Michael B Plaisted.  William T. Berens appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Case set for Plea & Sentencing.
AS TO COUNT 3
Pursuant to plea negotiations, on a motion of the state the court amended Count 3 to REMOVE the Use of a Dangerous Weapon enhancer, 939.63(1)(a).  Probation Review Hearing scheduled for November 20, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
